description: For sale: $124,900. One-level living at its best! This modern condo has a brand new kitchen, tastefully and beautifully finished with soft-close drawers, tiled backsplash, brand new solid cabinetry, brand new stainless steel appliances, quartz countertops, and new flooring. Gorgeous! Lots of space in the living room to include an office desk or additional furniture. Refinished three-season porch with screened windows all around. All the tasteful updates include a new vanity countertop in the bathroom and new flooring throughout the home. Be a part of a great community, take a walk to Lake Cornelia. Be close to everything Edina and Minneapolis have to offer and never be far from home!
Zestimate® Home Value: $465,127.

For sale: $229,000. Exceptional sought after first-floor corner unit in the "Hampshire" Building. Bright and sunny, fresh and clean. This unit has been completely repainted and carpeted, with new stainless finishing off the kitchen. Enjoy summer evenings on the spacious patio area overlooking the gardens. Convenience and comfort await.
Zestimate® Home Value: $527,761.

description: For sale: $589,000. MUST SEE hard to find large Edina home on an oversized lot with an amazing backyard.  House has been updated from top to bottom.  Kitchen updates include: an amazing open concept design with premium appliances, large center island to sit at, hardwood floors throughout, floor to ceiling cabinets, and granite countertops.  Bathroom updates include: 6 foot and 5 foot jetted tubs, new tile throughout, heated tile floors, new cabinets, granite countertops, and two rainfall shower heads in the lower level bath.  3 large bedrooms on the main level, and 2 large bedrooms on the lower level.  There is a washer dryer on the main level and lower level for added convenience of doing multiple loads at the same time.  2 fireplaces for comfortable lounging on each level of the home. The house was repainted inside and outside over the past year, along with a new roof in 2019.  Huge utility room for storage.  Just 1 block from Cornelia Elementary School, and minutes from Edina shopping and restaurants.

description:
For sale: $225,000. Property vacant and available for safe showings!  WELCOME HOME! This South and East facing 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom condo features an open floor plan with new
carpet, new entryway and kitchen flooring, fresh paint throughout and plenty of sun. The large master bedroom offers a 3/4 bath, walk-in closet, and a private door leading to the balcony. The 3rd bedroom, located off the living room area, can be re-purposed as a den and also has a private door to the balcony. Shared amenities include:  indoor heated pool, community room, exercise room, laundry room and patio with gas grill.  Prime location near many great Edina shops, restaurants, and airport.

For sale: $280,000. Private showings available by appointment only!

This beautiful 2 bedroom, 1 & 3/4 bathroom one-level condo is in a highly desirable location in the heart of Edina, MN -  just within a block from Fairview Hospital and the Southdale Shopping Center. Recently remodeled with new floors, bathrooms and kitchen. Features include a large kitchen, floor-to-ceiling windows, and a paved, private patio with walkout access from the Family Room and the Living Room. Pets are allowed, number and size restrictions apply. Owners and guests can enjoy a beautiful pool area, community room, and large common areas. There are 4 secure access entries to this condo and an enclosed parking garage. Walking distance to restaurants, grocery stores, Lifetime Fitness, and the bus line!

description: Recently sold: $377,000. Welcome to this bright and spacious two bedroom, two bath condo at Point of France. Kitchen updated in 2015 and opened up for entertaining. Large bedrooms and walk-in closets, private master bath and dressing area. A den off the entry allows for a study or media area. Two underground garage stalls included with this lovely and private home. Laundry room updated with built-in cabinets, new washer and dryer. Shared amenities galore include indoor pool/whirlpool, workout room, guest suites, library, billiards room and more. come see all that entails living at Point of France. Close to restaurants, shopping, highways and airport. 24 hour security provides peace of mind. Full-time onsite management.

Recently sold: $680,000. Welcome home to this thoughtfully redesigned 4 bedroom, 4 bath with a brilliant use of vaults, expansive windows and skylights throughout to maximize that every spacious room is enveloped in natural light. Soaring two-story foyer opens to the airy living room featuring marble surround wood-burning fireplace, two main level bedrooms and beautiful full tiled bath with dual vanity granite countertop. Fantastic loft area shares the upper level space with the very private owner?s suite boasting two-sided marble fireplace, large walk-in closet and breathtaking remodeled full bath with floating dual sink honed granite vanity, air-jetted soaker tub and huge tiled shower. Outstanding informal living areas flow generously into the clean and crisp center island kitchen with abundance of  maple cabinetry, granite/Corian counters and high-end stainless appliances. Fantastic knotty pine sunroom addition in 2000 overlooks the idyllic backyard landscape surrounding the flagstone patio and raised decking, complete with stone fountain feature. The current owner of this immaculate home has remodeled and updated every inch in recent years offering maple hardwood flooring, oak woodwork, interior paint and ceilings, new windows/skylights/sliding doors; finished lower level family room, exercise room, generous size guest bedroom, sleek 3/4 bath, organized laundry room w/Asko washer (one year old) and dryer, plus much more. Attached two-car garage includes built-in workshop/bench, convenient storage room off upper loft area and spacious closets throughout. Tucked away in a quiet Edina neighborhood, only a half block to access Lake Cornelia nature trails, Rosland Park and Edina Aquatic Center; only minutes to The Galleria, Southdale Mall, Target, Whole Foods, Byerly?s, Trader Joe?s and a multitude of retail/restaurants. Truly a must see property!

Recently sold: $165,000. Current owner of 23 years has lovingly cared for this high demand 1st floor condo and has made  many updates and improvements. Kitchen has beautiful cabinets with new hardware including  hinges completed in 2018. New Corian countertops, sink, backsplash, and paint in 2018! Bathroom updated in 2018 with new Corian top, sink, faucet...bath is ceramic tile shower & floor! Condo has 6 panel white doors & princeton type trim. Entire condo was painted in 2018! New blinds 2019. New washer & dryer in 2019. Both wall AC units are updated. Updated ceiling fan in dining area. This beautiful condo is a short stroll to Edinborough indoor park with JR. Olympic sized pool, walking/running paths, exercise equipment, locker rooms and more all included in association dues. Centennial Lakes park is also one block from condo!

The high end, center island kitchen features a walk-in pantry and functional design that maximizes views and enables tidiness while entertaining. BR suites are located on opposing ends of the unit; the master with balcony includes a built-in dresser, excellent closet space and BA with Carrara marble, while the guest BR with ensuite BA is presently used as a den.  Powder BA and laundry round out in-unit features. 2 garage spaces across from elevator plus convenient storage nearby. A tunnel to Galleria stores and Starbucks is perfect for cold winter mornings. description:
Recently sold: $108,000. I am offering my condo in the heart of Edina for sale. If you're looking for quick access to the bus, easy walk to shopping and a 5 minute drive to all the major highways you'd love this place!

 It's a one bedroom one bathroom condo. With newer carpet, hardwood floors and updated cabinets. This unit has more cupboard and storage space than many of the other units in the building. The pantry also adds substantial storage with slide out drawers. 

 The condo overlooks the courtyard. You'll have access to an outdoor pool (in the summer), sauna, workout room and access to a party room (all season). There is assigned underground heated parking. The storage unit is on the same floor as the condo and is climate controlled. 

 The association fees cover, hear, outside maintenance, exterior insurance, gas, water, sewer and cable television through Comcast. The building has secured entry on all the doors and has an onsite building manager. 

 This is a great place if you're looking to downsize, own your first home or would prefer to pay less than renting (and have tax benefits).

 I have an assumable mortgage and there is the option of taking over the mortgage with the current and remaining terms. I refinanced it a few years ago so the rate is very competitive. You'd have to qualify for an FHA mortgage so somewhere decent credit would be needed. Why do this? You can own the property with about 3.5 years knocked off the mortgage and you wouldn't need to use your cash for down payment. Cash offers or your own financing are also welcome.

 If you're serious about learning more please let me know what questions I could answer for you or discuss showing the property.

 ALL REASONABLE OFFERS WILL BE CONSIDERED. Quick close available.

For sale: $280,000. Private showings available by appointment only!

description:
Recently sold: $192,500. Sunny and spacious 2BD/2BA condo available now. Located in a prime location near Centennial Lakes, the Galleria, Southdale Mall, Whole Foods, Byerly s, Starbucks, MSP Int l Airport, walking trails, hospitals, and more! Unit was recently updated and includes NEW Stainless-steel kitchen appliances, cabinets, counter tops, and lighting. New carpet in living spaces and fresh paint throughout. This unit has vaulted ceilings and a main floor open-concept layout. The master bedroom, walk-in closet, and a full bath are located on the second floor. In-unit washer/dryer, tons of storage/closet space, two underground heated garage spots, and cable are all included in monthly rent. Additional perks -- Enjoy a private balcony that overlooks a beautiful green space and in-unit gas fireplace. Tenants also get access to Edinborough Park amenities including: a playground, banquet room, amphitheater, indoor pool, track, and workout room. Tenants only pay electricity and internet. Cats allowed with a $500 non-refundable pet deposit. Minimum 1-year lease, application fee is $40 per person. If approved, 1 months rent deposit is due and first months rent is due upon move-in. 
Available now, inquire today!

Tenants pay electric and internet.

Security deposit is equal to 1 month s rent.  Minimum 12 month lease.  The association require a one time $200 move in fee. Sorry, no smoking, no pets allowed, and no Section 8. $50 non-refundable application/Background/Credit check fee per adult.  Prefer good credit. Income must be verifiable.
